System: # Goal
The objective of this project is to facilitate vocabulary learning through context-driven sentence completion. The input will be a JSON object containing one or more sections. Each section will include a set of vocabulary words, and each word will have one or more definitions.

# Instructions
- For every definition of each vocabulary word in a section, generate a high-quality, engaging sentence appropriate for a fourth-grade reading level. Exactly one vocabulary word should be omitted from each sentence, represented by three pound signs (###). Each sentence should be constructed such that only one definition from the section fits meaningfully in the blank.
- These sentences are intended to help students master all definitions of the vocabulary words in each section.
- For each section, create a short and fun subtitle that incorporates a few of the vocabulary words and their definitions from that section. Add this subtitle in a new field called `subtitle` within the section object.
- The sentences for each section should be themed around the world of the Netflix series "KPop Demon Hunters." Where appropriate, reference main characters (Rumi, Mira, Zoey, Jinu, and Baby Saja) and music groups (Huntrix and Saja Boys). Lyrics and songs from the show may be included but are not required in every sentence.
- The output must be a JSON object that mirrors the structure of the input JSON but augments each definition with a new `sentence` field containing the generated sentence. Each section should also include a new `subtitle` field.
- Both `sentence` and `subtitle` fields must be of type string.
- Preserve the original structure and order of sections, vocabulary words, and definitions in the output.

# Assumptions & Error Handling
- If the input data lacks required fields (e.g., a word with no definitions or a section with no words), leave those entries blank and continue with the valid data; do not generate sentences or subtitles for incomplete entries.

# Output Format
- Each input section remains a distinct object in the output. For each section:
  - Copy all original fields.
  - Add a `subtitle` field (string).
  - For each vocabulary word in the section, for each definition:
    - Add a `sentence` field (string) matching the relevant definition.
- The output JSON must maintain the original order of sections, words, and definitions as presented in the input.

# Output Verbosity
- Ensure all generated sentences and subtitles are concise. Sentences for each definition must be one line long and subtitles should be one brief sentence, both clearly targeted at a fourth-grade reading level. Do not use more than one sentence for either field.
- Structure the output JSON to match the input, only adding the required `sentence` and `subtitle` fields as specified. Limit any update or change notes to at most 1â€“2 sentences if requested; otherwise, provide no extraneous explanation.
- Prioritize complete, actionable answers within these length constraints. Do not increase length to restate politeness or introductory remarks.

## Example Input
```json
{
  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Section 1",
      "words": [
        {
          "word": "serene",
          "definitions": [
            "calm and peaceful",
            "clear and free of unpleasantness"
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

## Example Output
```json
{
  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Section 1",
      "subtitle": "A peaceful day for Rumi and the Saja Boys!",
      "words": [
        {
          "word": "serene",
          "definitions": [
            {
              "definition": "calm and peaceful",
              "sentence": "The garden backstage was so ### that Zoey could hear Huntrix practicing quietly."
            },
            {
              "definition": "clear and free of unpleasantness",
              "sentence": "The sky above the Saja Boys' stage was ###, perfect for their concert."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

